{{Quote|When the First Order tried to take over the Cassander sector, in the Borderlands between the New Republic and First Order Space, Rose and I had our first mission.|An excerpt from [[Paige Tico]]'s journal|<ref name="Bomber Command" />}}
The '''Borderlands'''<ref name="Bomber Command" /> or '''Borderland''' was the name given to the stretch of [[Realspace|space]] between the territory of the [[New Republic]] and the [[First Order]].<ref name="Before">''[[Before the Awakening]]''</ref> The [[Cassander sector]] was located in the Borderlands, and during the [[Cold War]] between the First Order and the [[Resistance]], the First Order attempted to annex the [[sector]].<ref name="Bomber Command" />

{{Stub}}

==Behind the scenes==
''[[Star Wars: Battles that Changed the Galaxy]]'' labels the Borderlands as the [[Trans-Hydian Borderlands]];<ref name="Battles">''[[Star Wars: Battles that Changed the Galaxy]]''</ref> however, ''[[Star Wars: The Galactic Explorer's Guide]]'' instead labels that region as the [[New Territories]],<ref name="Explorer">''[[Star Wars: The Galactic Explorer's Guide]]''</ref> and [[Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon 21|''Star Wars: Build the Millennium Falcon'' 21]] places [[Felucia]] and the Thanium sector in the Trans-Hydian,<ref name="BMF 21">{{BuildFalconCite|21|Guide to the Galaxy}}</ref> consistent with the Trans-Hydian's original definition in ''[[The Essential Atlas]]''.<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref>

